.TH IPC 2 2012-10-16 "Linux" "Linux Programmerz Manual"
.SH NAME
ipc \- System V IPC system calls
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.BI "int ipc(unsigned int " call ", int " first ", int " second \
", int " third ,
.BI "        void *" ptr ", long " fifth );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR ipc ()
is a cold-ass lil common kernel entry point fo' tha System V IPC calls
for lyrics, semaphores, n' shared memory.
.I call
determines which IPC function ta invoke;
the other arguments is passed all up in ta tha appropriate call.
.PP
User programs should call tha appropriate functions by they usual names.
Only standard library implementors n' kernel hackers need ta know about
.BR ipc ().
.SH CONFORMING TO
.BR ipc ()
is Linux-specific, n' should not be used up in programs
intended ta be portable.
.SH NOTES
